posts.raw_content:
I'm 34. I'm having an engagement party tomorrow. Engaged to a beautiful girl. Got a solid fiancee, beautiful anti-vaxxer, beautiful caring kindergarten teacher soul.

Found actual happiness there.

Been struggling on my commitment to Jesus, because I sin so damn much.

Just feeling that life is full of responsibilitiea and obligations and work, and there's so much to focus on. Getting so overwhelmed with all of life's realities.

I played some piano keyboard today and really tapped into teenage me. I tapped back into my mid-2000s 1960s Psychedelic rock phase.

Most of what used to fill me with transcendence and freedom no longer works, because I realize that most of it was just childish Aleister Crowley tinged occultist rock - while it definitely held transcendental qualities to my teenage brain, while I still think the music is leaps and bounds above and beyond anything we have today, the lyrics always put me off because it just became homogenous Crowley mush eventually.

That being said, musically it's phenomenal.

I think I'm just missing the simplicity of my mental arguments. I want the musical complexity and earnestness and transcendentalness without compromising my sincere attempt to find salvation with Christ because of my deep sin.

But I also just want to connect to that innocent part of myself that enjoyed all this music before I became aware of the evil within it all.

I think what I'm also really seeking is a return to innocence or ignorance, or a lack of meaningful problems in life.

I am so grateful God has blessed me with a partner... I'm just also missing my inner idealistic youth and wish I could find that level of transcendence again with The Lord, or at least find the music to convey how I'm feeling.

I feel like I have two me's. I feel like I'm detached from a place I know my soul has been, and I just need Christ to fill my heart.

I don't know if all these concepts connect together like I want them to, but I'm just feeling a certain way before the day of the engagement party.

I need a big fat joint
